We're like, "That didn't get that scratch."And so we'll go to the next thing and we'll keep listening and listening to sermons until we find the right one.

00:22:40.072 --> 00:22:46.488
And we're like, "Oh, that was it! That was it! That was it!"And we'll pick it like a chicken on a bone.

00:22:46.489 --> 00:22:56.247
We'll go and pick through that thing. I told her, I said, "We're scavengers. We don't depend on our pastors to feed us spiritually.

00:22:56.248 --> 00:23:04.079
You don't need to depend on your pastors to feed you spiritually."How desperate are you for your life to change?

00:23:04.080 --> 00:23:10.086
If you're waiting on your pastor to preach a sermon behind the pulpit to change your life, you're missing it.

00:23:10.087 --> 00:23:16.262
You go there to just get a refilling. You just get a little bit extra, a nugget.

00:23:16.263 --> 00:23:20.270
You glean from it, and you listen and you know that you're staying on track.

00:23:20.271 --> 00:23:27.157
You have some spiritual somebody there to help you out, and you get refreshed just being in that atmosphere.

00:23:27.158 --> 00:23:35.124
Yeah, being together—they're family. But I don't go to our church to get spiritually fed. No.

00:23:35.125 --> 00:23:41.094
If I'm waiting for them to give me something spiritually on just Sundays or Wednesdays, I'm going to starve.

00:23:41.095 --> 00:23:48.178
By that time, you're going to be anemic. Because I go, "Man, and that's not fair to them.""Well, you know what?

00:23:48.179 --> 00:23:53.754
That meal wasn't very good, Pastor. I'm in trouble until next week."We eat twice a week?

00:23:53.755 --> 00:24:03.594
No, no way. There's so many people that are doing that. And that's why I think if it was—in fact, when I go there, I'm already full.

00:24:03.595 --> 00:24:11.077
Yeah, I'm already full. I'm going, Diana needs to pat me on my back because spiritually I'm perfect because I've already eaten all day long.

00:24:11.078 --> 00:24:17.998
And I'm like, "Where are we going tonight?"Oh, yeah. Because we're worshiping the Lord. We're giving Him some time. We're honoring Him.

00:24:17.999 --> 00:24:25.293
But I'm not going for Pastor Chip and Candace to make sure they feed us or whatever, because we're dumping out on this channel all the time.

00:24:25.294 --> 00:24:30.879
And we go, "What do we do?"But what I'm trying to tell you all is that we find it for ourselves. We're scavengers.

00:24:30.880 --> 00:24:40.205
And it may just look like, you know, like they make that old gumbo and it looks like something that came out of a ditch, but I'm going to take it, and it's going to be good by the time we're done.

00:24:40.206 --> 00:24:47.433
You know what I'm saying? We're going to find it. Wherever it is, we're going to find it. We're going to pick the bones of this thing. And we pray.

00:24:47.434 --> 00:24:55.620
I pray every time I go on and I'm trying to search for a sermon—a good sermon, a Kenneth Hagin sermon, or whatever it is. I pray before and I say, "Holy Spirit, lead me.

00:24:55.621 --> 00:25:02.768
Lead me to the right one."I don't want to just listen to like five sermons that were just mediocre and finally on the sixth one, it's the one I want.

00:25:02.769 --> 00:25:09.906
Because there are some of them out there, even with them. Time is of the essence, and we don't always have a lot of time during our day.

00:25:09.907 --> 00:25:22.966
So, we have to make it count. She has found some honey. I mean, I'm telling you, I told her, "You've found some good ones today, babe."We sat in the car; I didn't want to get out of the car.

00:25:22.967 --> 00:25:30.833
I told her, "I started weeping. Hold on a minute. This one right here—can we rewind that?"And she's like, "Fast forward, fast forward."And we listened to it again.

00:25:30.834 --> 00:25:38.879
And I said, "Oh, take notes on it."She got this little thing—it's a little recorder. She pushes the button when the Lord's giving me a word now.

00:25:38.880 --> 00:25:48.046
She has to have her phone; she goes "bing"and she gets those words recorded because there are nuggets that will change your life if you grab onto them.

00:25:48.047 --> 00:25:57.620
When you value the Word, when the Word becomes everything you have, "I need this. I'm desperate.

00:25:57.621 --> 00:26:07.876
I have to have a touch from the Father today."And that's why she said we can't do those binge-watching of certain things that made us laugh in the past.

00:26:07.877 --> 00:26:18.169
We have to find the living Word because of where we are in these end times. This is how serious it is. This is wartime.

00:26:18.170 --> 00:26:30.154
The more you give into that tugging, that Holy Ghost tugging when He tugs you throughout the day, and whenever you listen to it and yield to that tugging, saying, "Okay, it's time to listen.

00:26:30.155 --> 00:26:35.205
It's time to put some Word on. Time to read the Bible,"the more you do it, it changes you.

00:26:35.206 --> 00:26:40.239
And I don't want to be the same person next year that I am right now. I want to constantly be changing.

00:26:40.240 --> 00:26:47.048
We're never going to say we've achieved it all, that we are where we're supposed to be spiritually, or that we're more spiritual than anybody else.

00:26:47.049 --> 00:26:50.629
We're never going to be that person, but we're always going to strive.

00:26:50.630 --> 00:27:07.695
I press on in this race of the high calling to finish my course, like that scripture says: "I have fought the good fight, I have finished my course, I have kept the faith."I refuse to get up there and...

00:27:07.696 --> 00:27:14.306
What were you going to say? I was going to say, and sometimes I feel like maybe I need a little bit more than most people. Maybe I'm a little more clingy.

00:27:14.307 --> 00:27:23.110
Maybe I'm like, "Lord, I need You so much right now."One little thing in my day and I'm like, "Daddy, I need help today.

00:27:23.111 --> 00:27:32.448
This has been rough."And I just cling. So, that's just how I get by. It's on Him.

00:27:32.449 --> 00:27:37.030
Being filled with and controlled by the Holy Ghost, being desperate for that feeling.

00:27:37.031 --> 00:27:44.523
I need You right now, and I can't do this life without You. I don't know how anybody can do it.

00:27:44.524 --> 00:27:52.296
The darker it gets, how are they able to do life without Jesus?

00:27:52.297 --> 00:28:02.157
That's why maybe they are talking to ChatGPT and trying to find stuff and trying to find that inward peace, because they don't have anything else.

00:28:02.158 --> 00:28:09.091
But it's like I heard Billy Burke say in one of his sermons, he was talking about how whenever he's walking around...

00:28:09.092 --> 00:28:19.670
He said that's why people go to Disney World and that's why people go to concerts: there's a presence and they're trying to fill that void.

00:28:19.671 --> 00:28:23.689
They go there because that's what they're trying to serve. They don't even ride the rides.

00:28:23.690 --> 00:28:33.354
He said, "I live by there and we go there and just walk around and we watch people, and ninety percent of them don't ever even get on a ride.

00:28:33.355 --> 00:28:46.961
They just want to feel the atmosphere of Disney World."And then they go to a football game because they're trying to submerge themselves in that atmosphere, but it only lasts for an hour or two, and then it's over.

00:28:46.962 --> 00:29:02.009
And then what are you left with? So, it's just people throughout the world constantly trying to get into a presence that fills something in them.

00:29:02.010 --> 00:29:18.740
That's why we wanted to make a place here for people to come and drink, for people to come and get refreshed on a day-to-day basis, because we know what it's like to be a scavenger and go. Maybe this could be your oasis.

00:29:18.741 --> 00:29:51.594
I told her, "Maybe we could be the oasis for them, that we bring an atmosphere, a place for them to get refreshed, that they come and they hear there's hope."Yeah, there's judgment, these things the Lord's showing me that are not too fun sometimes, but it's still telling you that Jesus Christ is coming back soon, and He has a plan for your life to bless you, to heal you, to prosper you, to give you an expected future and hope, and that we can pray together and change things through prayer.

00:29:51.595 --> 00:29:57.482
I just believe that when I'm telling you about these grounds, people don't know this stuff.

00:29:57.483 --> 00:30:03.889
We've done this through trial and error. I'm forty-five, and it doesn't matter how old she is.

00:30:03.890 --> 00:30:10.289
She's young. I'm teasing with you. It's nobody's business, right?

00:30:10.290 --> 00:30:16.819
But I'm just saying, that's what Kathryn Kuhlman says: we don't tell women's age.

00:30:16.820 --> 00:30:26.796
But I'm saying there's a lot of people that are desperate and they're wanting just a touch from the Lord.

00:30:26.797 --> 00:30:41.220
They come to that place of dryness and they say, "God, where are you in this dryness?"And that's why I've tried to teach you my nuggets of where we've learned to sew, how we've learned to do things, and it works for us, and we see fruit.

00:30:41.221 --> 00:30:49.421
But a lot of people keep doing the same thing over and over again, and they're still broke.

00:30:49.422 --> 00:30:52.430
They're not going anywhere spiritually, and they're expecting different results.

00:30:52.431 --> 00:31:00.285
And if I don't see results in that ground the first two or three times, I'm not going to give there anymore.

00:31:00.286 --> 00:31:06.275
We said to keep doing the same thing and expecting different results is insanity. And if you don't see fruit...

00:31:06.276 --> 00:31:12.238
It's like when we were doing things with Megan, we would try stuff for a couple of months trying to get her help with therapy.

00:31:12.239 --> 00:31:17.569
And if we didn't see... because we only have a limited amount of money for her to have therapy, right?

00:31:17.570 --> 00:31:30.438
So, instead of trying to keep doing this over a year because we're running out of time and she's getting older and older, you go, "This isn't working."And instead, we just tell the therapist, "You know what?

00:31:30.439 --> 00:31:41.750
We've given you ninety days, and we haven't seen any results of anything really significant with doing certain medical protocols or whatever to help my daughter."We don't mean no offense to you.

00:31:41.751 --> 00:31:46.762
We know you've helped other people, but this isn't for us, and we have to say we're done, right?

00:31:46.763 --> 00:31:55.229
Yeah, we're the same with supplements and everything else. We've done diets, supplements, all different things.

00:31:55.230 --> 00:32:00.614
Some of it may have helped some, but if we didn't see enough progress, we just don't have enough.

00:32:00.615 --> 00:32:08.279
Especially if it's draining your finances and you are limited to a certain amount of finances, what you're believing for at that time or where your job is at instead.

00:32:08.280 --> 00:32:13.309
So you go, "Well, I'm believing God for extra until that extra comes to add that to that puzzle. I can't.

00:32:13.310 --> 00:32:23.594
This isn't a significant enough change to keep going down this road."So what I'm trying to tell you is, with your spiritual walk, you have to have a spiritual thermostat.

00:32:23.595 --> 00:32:29.558
Yes, have a spiritual thermostat of what's working. Is this working?

00:32:29.559 --> 00:32:35.173
Is this changing me? Am I coming up higher spiritually or do I feel deflated?

00:32:35.174 --> 00:32:46.374
If my pastor is not helping me even a little bit and I'm not getting anything from that church, maybe it's time to look for a new church. Does that make sense?

00:32:46.375 --> 00:32:58.903
If my kids are in the youth group and the youth leader is not good, or your children's church pastor or whatever, and your kids aren't growing spiritually or they're not changing, look and evaluate spiritually of where you are.

00:32:58.904 --> 00:33:05.308
And I'm not telling you it's not the pastor's fault on everything, you know what I'm saying?

00:33:05.309 --> 00:33:15.278
You have to evaluate you. What are you doing to grow yourself spiritually? Are you getting something from there?

00:33:15.279 --> 00:33:24.513
And if God has called you there to help out there or whatever, have you done what He's called you to do? Have you grown?

00:33:24.514 --> 00:33:33.475
If you're not going from glory to glory and you're at a church and you go, "You know, they don't believe in the baptism of the Holy Ghost,"for one, I'd be out of there.

00:33:33.476 --> 00:33:47.759
If they don't believe in the baptism of the Holy Ghost, if they don't believe in divine healing and they'll lay hands on you, it's like I heard one preacher say, "You'll believe in healing whenever you're desperate and you have stage four cancer."That's what Billy Burke said.

00:33:47.760 --> 00:33:55.725
He goes, "Yeah, told me, 'I don't believe God can heal.'Well, you're not sick enough."If you're overcoming something really bad, you're going to believe something desperate.

00:33:55.726 --> 00:34:03.469
You'll believe. But what kind of cart are you attaching your horses to?

00:34:03.470 --> 00:34:10.711
I don't want to attach to people that don't believe in divine healing, that don't believe in laying hands on the sick.

00:34:10.712 --> 00:34:16.865
And if I'm overcoming something, they're going, "You know, sometimes God does and sometimes He doesn't, brother.

00:34:16.866 --> 00:34:20.708
It might be your time to go home."I don't want that in my corner.

00:34:20.709 --> 00:34:33.220
I want somebody to go there and say, "I believe God with you, and I'm standing with you that you're healed by the stripes of Jesus, and you're going to get healed,"and try to speak life into me.

00:34:33.221 --> 00:34:48.398
And believes in praying in tongues. Believes in teaching my kids to live a holy lifestyle and that they've got what it takes to make it in this world in school, and cast out devils if you've got a devil or whatever.

00:34:48.399 --> 00:35:01.750
Not, "Well, you know what? I don't really believe that you can have a devil."No, I'm telling you, I've seen Christians flat out say they're born again, growling and acting crazy with a demonic spirit attached to their soulish realm.

00:35:01.751 --> 00:35:14.596
No, it's not attached to their spirit. But I'm telling you, I've seen demonic attachments onto folks that are born-again believers, and they are growling, acting crazy, and manifested right there.

00:35:14.597 --> 00:35:18.488
And you've got to get them free because it's coming out of the mind, will, and the emotions.

00:35:18.489 --> 00:35:21.498
Your spirit is renewed, and all that happens with your spirit, right?

00:35:21.499 --> 00:35:26.191
But your body has stuff that has attachments. Alcohol addiction, pornography...

00:35:26.192 --> 00:35:32.239
you open a door for the devil to come in to kill, steal, and destroy you, and you get attachments.

00:35:32.240 --> 00:35:37.519
And I call them little—they're little boogeymen that go lay on your shoulder, and you've got to get free from that stuff.

00:35:37.520 --> 00:35:43.199
And if you read Pigs in the Parlor and these other books, they'll help you.

00:35:43.200 --> 00:35:47.582
But I don't get into the demonic stuff. I don't give them any place. I don't even talk about the demonic.

00:35:47.583 --> 00:36:01.505
But there's some people that need to know when it comes to addictions through pornography, through drugs, alcohol, any kind of perversion, the devil will, if you open the door, he's going to set up shop in your life.

00:36:01.506 --> 00:36:05.468
If you don't fill yourself up, they come back more. They come and try to torment your mind.

00:36:05.469 --> 00:36:09.273
They try to do all, and you've got to get your mind renewed in this Word.

00:36:09.274 --> 00:36:14.479
You cannot just pray in the spirit over demonic stuff and think you're going to get freedom.

00:36:14.480 --> 00:36:22.145
The Bible is the sword. You've got to speak this sword out of your mouth and cut that devil.

00:36:22.146 --> 00:36:27.850
But it's the truth. You know, the Bible says you know the truth and the truth will set you free.

00:36:27.851 --> 00:36:34.129
The only freedom and the truth, the only thing that's ever going to set you free is knowing this truth: the truth of the Word of God.

00:36:34.130 --> 00:36:41.138
The Word of God inside of your mouth is sharper than any two-edged sword, and it goes out of your mouth, and true freedom comes from the Word and cuts that devil.

00:36:41.139 --> 00:36:45.595
But if you're just praying in the spirit—"God, Jesus, thank you, Lord.

00:36:45.596 --> 00:37:02.799
Father, I just thank you, Lord"—it says, "If ye abide in me and my words remain in you, you shall ask what you will and it shall be done unto you."But you have to get the Word abiding in you and His words remaining.

00:37:02.800 --> 00:37:10.678
"If ye abide in me and my words remain in you, you shall ask what you will and it shall be done."So you have to get this Word inside of you speaking.

00:37:10.679 --> 00:37:20.210
We are speaking spirits. We are speaking forth this Word out of our mouth, and that's what changes you. And the devil knows when you know the truth.

00:37:20.211 --> 00:37:47.887
The devil knows when you know who you are, instead of saying verses of "Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star, how I wonder what you are."You can say a word and quote scripture, and I can read it one time: "Devil, this is what the Bible says."He knows the Word better than you do, but it's the truth that you know inside of you, that you have a Rhema word on the inside of you that's going to set you free.

00:37:47.888 --> 00:38:09.759
Like 2 Timothy 1:7: "God has not given me a spirit of fear, but of power and of love and of a sound mind."Getting that Word down inside of your heart, and that's how you'll know the truth and the truth will set you free.

00:38:09.760 --> 00:38:19.036
I've seen devil-casting-out services. There's all this stuff, and they go through the healing line, but they fall out, laid out.

00:38:19.037 --> 00:38:27.759
They have a courtesy fall or whatever, and they get out. But as Diana said, "I don't want to fall just to fall. I want to get up different.

00:38:27.760 --> 00:38:37.451
I want impartation."But the only thing that's truly going to give you impartation is the Word, understanding the Word of God.

00:38:37.452 --> 00:38:41.368
And I'm telling you, when you open the door for sin, you open the door for the devil.

00:38:41.369 --> 00:38:47.851
He's going to come right in. But this is the only thing that's going to keep you free. And that's just like they say, the Word works if you work it.

00:38:47.852 --> 00:38:52.479
And when you find scripture that pertains to you, that's something you're believing for.

00:38:52.480 --> 00:38:59.832
Another thing that we do is we write it down on sticky notes and we put it on the mirror or maybe under your visor of your car.

00:38:59.833 --> 00:39:09.596
I read one story about this man who was trying to recover from smoking cigarettes, and he had a scripture that he spoke every time that pertained to smoking cigarettes.

00:39:09.597 --> 00:39:19.015
He would flip his visor down and he had it written down on a little sticky, and every time he had the thought about smoking a cigarette, he would quote that scripture.

00:39:19.016 --> 00:39:27.408
And that's how it gets down inside of you. But it is only the truth that you know that will set you free.

00:39:27.409 --> 00:39:36.656
It's not just reading it once. Faith cometh by hearing, and hearing by the word of God over and over again.

00:39:36.657 --> 00:39:44.645
And I know that you will know the truth, and the truth will make you free and set you free.

00:39:44.646 --> 00:39:54.799
And I believe that's why so many people in the body of Christ live so bound with all these addictions.

00:39:54.800 --> 00:40:03.688
We're not made to live bound. God made us to have an abundant life, to the full, until it overflows.

00:40:03.689 --> 00:40:14.959
And if you're not living abundantly in finances, health, prosperity, and mental clarity, you have to go back and check your word gauge.

00:40:14.960 --> 00:40:23.044
Where is my word level? Is it the pastor's fault? Well, that's Pastor Chip's fault.

00:40:23.045 --> 00:40:26.109
It's probably Pastor T's fault; she didn't preach a good enough word this week.

00:40:26.110 --> 00:40:30.959
No, it's not their fault. It's not the fault of the people you go to.

00:40:30.960 --> 00:40:35.914
It's your fault. You have 24 hours in a day, seven days a week, just like I do.

00:40:35.915 --> 00:40:41.596
We all have the opportunity to turn on something on YouTube or whatever—a word, a preaching sermon.

00:40:41.597 --> 00:40:52.971
We listen to Kenneth Hagin a lot and listen to his old stuff—find stuff clear back in the '80s and munch on that and go, 'Was that good?

00:40:52.972 --> 00:40:58.003
It's okay. Next one.'You know, and go, 'Boy, that was good. Let's find it.

00:40:58.004 --> 00:41:03.039
Let's keep listening to it.'There's one that I told her, 'We've got to go over it again and again.'I listened to one this week.

00:41:03.040 --> 00:41:08.712
It was an old camp meeting, and John Osteen—Dad Osteen—was there preaching. He was talking.

00:41:08.713 --> 00:41:14.750
I said, 'My God, it was wonderful.'And I told her, 'That was one of my favorite sermons I've heard in a long time.

00:41:14.751 --> 00:41:20.251
We've got to listen to it again.'And it was a wonderful sermon from the '80s.

00:41:20.252 --> 00:41:30.383
The old ones are good. He's more real, you know? I love it when it's raw. It's just raw because there's just something about it.

00:41:30.384 --> 00:41:40.935
I don't know, when you hear somebody talking—I don't like performance, and I'm not saying Brother Hagin ever was performance, but there are certain sermons when you listen to people where you go, 'I don't want performance.

00:41:40.936 --> 00:41:59.279
I'm not here for you to entertain me. Give me something to bust that devil in the head today so that we can go from glory to glory.'But Diana and I, we're just like, 'Where is a chicken?'We're going, I mean, and to the vegans, 'Where is a good lettuce head?

00:41:59.280 --> 00:42:07.970
Where's a good cabbage?'I don't know, whatever you eat. But I like chicken myself, and I'm going to look for some chicken instead of a lettuce head for the vegans.

00:42:07.971 --> 00:42:16.719
Or some tofu. Where's some tofu? I'm just going to find something that's going to make some meat on my bones spiritually.

00:42:16.720 --> 00:42:21.959
And tofu doesn't settle with me—I'm just being real with y'all.

00:42:21.960 --> 00:42:28.601
God loves everybody. He gave me chicken to eat, too, God bless it.

00:42:28.602 --> 00:42:39.765
Chicken and dumplings! Woohoo! Whatever. But people get upset; I'm sure I'll get an email on that one. We know there's a great shaking to awaken.

00:42:39.766 --> 00:42:51.439
And if you don't have a backbone like a crowbar for what I see coming, if you don't know who you are, I told you Psalm 91 is not just a feel-good verse.

00:42:51.440 --> 00:43:00.366
'A thousand shall fall at my side, and ten thousand at my right hand; but it shall not come nigh me.'Well, thank God for me, but that means ten thousand falling at my hand—that's ten thousand dead.

00:43:00.367 --> 00:43:07.430
A thousand over here dead. That's a lot of folks. Something is going on around here.

00:43:07.432 --> 00:43:12.159
It's happening, and there are bad days. And that's what I'm trying to say.

00:43:12.160 --> 00:43:16.544
He's telling you He prepares a table before you in the presence of all your enemies.

00:43:16.545 --> 00:43:23.503
Standing on Psalm 91 in hard times, that means there are some people watching you eat who are trying to hurt you. But we're supposed to have no fear.

00:43:23.504 --> 00:43:30.822
He said His rod and His staff will comfort me, and surely goodness and mercy will follow me all the days of my life. Look at all of that verse.

00:43:30.823 --> 00:43:36.399
He's saying, 'No pestilence, no plagues will come nigh me.'That means there's a pestilence and a plague there.

00:43:36.400 --> 00:43:45.519
That means when they're talking about the death in Utah, the Black Death, or whatever they're talking about again, I'm trying to tell you all they're trying to get you ready.

00:43:45.520 --> 00:43:49.279
Something big is about to happen, but I'm not trying to tell you to get in fear.

00:43:49.280 --> 00:43:58.302
I'm trying to tell you to draw near. In California—yeah, don't get in fear, draw near.

00:43:58.303 --> 00:44:07.159
Get closer to Him because the storm's coming. Financial stuff's coming as they see all this stuff about the debt.

00:44:07.160 --> 00:44:15.837
Well, we hope Jerome Powell lowers interest rates in September. He's had such a stiff neck since the last administration.

00:44:15.838 --> 00:44:28.336
He's like, 'We're not lowering interest rates.''Well, you better.''No, we're not.''Well, I can't stand Trump.'And you go, it's all political, and you see what's going on.

00:44:28.337 --> 00:44:30.552
But I'm telling you all, I ain't worried about Jerome Powell.

00:44:30.553 --> 00:44:35.039
I'm not participating in their economic system. You know which one I participate in?

